astic and monastic communities, and the exciting insights into lived monasticism through the archaeology of monasticism in Egypt.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAsceticismxChristianity. 0aChristian antiquitieszEgypt. 0aMonasticism and religious orderszEgyptxHistoryyEarly church, ca. 30-600. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Archaeology.2bisacsh  aDesert Fathers.  aEgypt.  aasceticism.  aearly Christianity.  alate antiquity.  amonasticism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023 Englishz978311131908708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023z9783111318110oZDB-23-DGD40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781802700817?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781802700817423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781802700817/original  a978-3-11-102374-8  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131908-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGDb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023